World Athletics spokeswoman Nicole Jeffery released a statement on Twitter regarding the visa situation. She attributed the visa challenges to the post-pandemic situation, saying, â€œThe Oregon22 organising committee and World Athletics are working closely with the USOPC to follow up on Visa applications, the majority of which have been successfully resolved. We continue to follow up with those outstanding visa issues.â€
However, the statement was not received well by some athletes. Retired world and Olympic gold medallist Michael Johnson responded to the statement as â€œpitiful and shamefulâ€.
Officials said that of the 5,500 participants and officials coming to Eugene, fewer than one percent still had visa issues on the eve of the championships. â€œWeâ€™ve battled to do as much as we possibly can,â€ World Athletics President Sebastian Coe said. â€œAnd weâ€™ve been doing this now for some months. And of course there are political complications about nations being able to travel and nations coming into the United States.â€
